Strange that the inner life of the child of God in Christ should have been ‘discovered’ as the aricle reveals…had it not already been disclosed through the life and example of He who reconciled and redeemed his people? Admittedly I had to ‘discover’ it for myself…and find it amazing and most irresponsible of me throughout my pastoral and secular ministries that there was a time when I thought myself too involved, too busy to attend to the disciplines of the inner life alongside of those of the outward calling to service. A word of encouragement, amid necessary sessions of ‘the dark nights of the soul’ persistent discipline of the inner life becomes a spiitual food which craves out of habit and without which any attempt to fulfil the outward calling in not only futile, but dangerous. Neverthe less I shall quote those pungent words of Howard Thurmond following 9-11 during my ministry of worship at Central Square Baptist Church this Sunday, Sept. 11, 2011. Ira Ellis, pastor
